<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.ToJson.toJson\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">ToJson</span>.<span class=\"name\">toJson</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.ToJson\">ToJson</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/Basic.html#Lean.Json\">Json</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.ToJson.toJson","kind":"def","line":75,"name":"Lean.ToJson.toJson","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.lean#L75-L75"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.ToJson.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">ToJson</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u} → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/Basic.html#Lean.Json\">Lean.Json</a>)</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.ToJson\">Lean.ToJson</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.ToJson.mk","kind":"ctor","line":35,"name":"Lean.ToJson.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.lean#L35-L75"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">class</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.ToJson\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">ToJson</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u</div></div>","info":{"doc":"Types that can be encoded as JSON.\n\nUse `deriving ToJson`\nto [automatically generate](https://lean-lang.org/doc/reference/4.33.0-rc1/find/?domain=Verso.Genre.Manual.section&name=deriving-instances) an instance.\nThe following encoding strategy is employed by auto-generated instances:\n\n* Basic types corresponding to JSON values are encoded as these values.\n\n  * `Bool` is encoded as `true`/`false`.\n\n  * `String`s are encoded as JSON strings.\n\n  * Numeric types are encoded as JSON numbers, with the exception of:\n\n    * `UInt64` and `USize`\n            which are encoded as JSON strings.\n            This is because, although JSON numbers proper have unbounded range,\n            in JavaScript they are parsed as [Number](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)s\n            and these can only represent integers up to $2^{53} - 1$ safely;\n            so a roundtrip through JavaScript would result in truncation on these types.\n            \\(We use these types in the JavaScript-based Lean infoview.\\)\n\n    * Special `Float`s which are encoded as JSON strings:\n            `\"NaN\"`/`\"Infinity\"`/`\"-Infinity\"`.\n\n* `Unit` is encoded as `{}` \\(empty JSON object\\).\n\n* `Array`s and `List`s are encoded as JSON arrays.\n\n* `Option.none` is encoded as `null`,\n    whereas  `some a` has the same encoding as `a`.\n    Note that this implies `Option (Option α)` does not roundtrip,\n    since `none` and `some none` both become `null`.\n\n* General `structure`s are encoded as JSON objects in the obvious way.\n\n  * `Option` fields whose names end with `?` have special support:\n        the question mark is omitted from the JSON field name,\n        and such a field is omitted from the JSON object when its value is `none`\n        \\(as opposed to being encoded as `{ \"someField\": null }`\\).\n\n* General `inductive` types are encoded on a per-constructor basis.\n\n  * An argument-free constructor is encoded as its name \\(a JSON string\\).\n\n  * A constructor with named arguments only is encoded as the JSON object\n        `{ \"ctorName\": { \"arg1\": argVal1, ..., \"argN\": argValN } }`.\n\n  * A constructor with one unnamed argument is encoded as the JSON object\n        `{ \"ctorName\": argVal }`.\n\n  * A constructor with more than one unnamed argument is encoded as the JSON object\n        `{ \"ctorName\": [argVal1, ..., argValN] }`.\n\n* Certain other types have special handling: see the instances below. ","docLink":"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.ToJson","kind":"class","line":35,"name":"Lean.ToJson","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.lean#L35-L75"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.FromJson.fromJson?\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">FromJson</span>.<span class=\"name\">fromJson?</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.FromJson\">FromJson</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/Basic.html#Lean.Json\">Json</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Except\">Except</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.FromJson.fromJson?","kind":"def","line":31,"name":"Lean.FromJson.fromJson?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.lean#L31-L31"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.FromJson.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">FromJson</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u} → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/Basic.html#Lean.Json\">Lean.Json</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Except\">Except</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.FromJson\">Lean.FromJson</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.FromJson.mk","kind":"ctor","line":22,"name":"Lean.FromJson.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.lean#L22-L31"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">class</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.FromJson\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">FromJson</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u</div></div>","info":{"doc":"Types that can be decoded from JSON.\n\nUse `deriving FromJson`\nto [automatically generate](https://lean-lang.org/doc/reference/4.33.0-rc1/find/?domain=Verso.Genre.Manual.section&name=deriving-instances) an instance.\nSee `ToJson`\nfor details of auto-generated instances.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.html#Lean.FromJson","kind":"class","line":22,"name":"Lean.FromJson","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Data/Json/FromToJson/Basic.lean#L22-L31"}}],"imports":["Init.Data.Array.GetLit","Init.Data.ToString.Macro","Lean.Data.Json.Printer"],"instances":[{"className":"Lean.FromJson","name":"Lean.instFromJsonJson","typeNames":["Lean.Json"]},{"className":"Lean.ToJson","name":"Lean.instToJsonJson","typeNames":["Lean.Json"]},{"className":"Lean.FromJson","name":"Lean.instFromJsonJsonNumber","typeNames":["Lean.JsonNumber"]},{"className":"Lean.ToJson","name":"Lean.instToJsonJsonNumber","typeNames":["Lean.JsonNumber"]},{"className":"Lean.FromJson","name":"Lean.instFromJsonUnit","typeNames":["Unit"]},{"className":"Lean.ToJson","name":"Lean.instToJsonUnit","typeNames":["Unit"]},{"className":"Lean.FromJson","name":"Lean.instFromJsonEmpty","typeNames":["Empty"]},{"className":"Lean.ToJson","name":"Lean.instToJsonEmpty","typeNa